"I Know You Want Me (Calle Ocho)" is a song by rapper Pitbull released as the second single from his upcoming album, Rebelution. The song is a remix of "75, Brazil Street" by Nicola Fasano Vs Pat Rich, which itself samples "Street Player" by Chicago. The title is a reference to the Miami street Calle Ocho.

The official music video was released on March 9, 2009 from Ultra Records onand to date the video has received over 23,000,000 views, is the 5th most viewed "electronic" music video of all time and the 60th top favourited music video of all time.

The single has so far peaked at #2 on the Billboard Hot 100 in the U.S, making it Pitbull's most successful single to date and his first top 10 hit. In the UK the single debuted at #53 then raising to #28 the following week.

Rebelution is the fourth studio album by Miami rapper Pitbull, set to be released on September 1, 2009.
